name: microservices
description: This project demonstrates how to build a resilient, scalable microservices system with key Spring Cloud features.

name: ticketpond-backend-nx
description: Microservice architecture based ticket selling system

name: kitchen-microservices
description: a web microservice system for ordering and showing/(un)finishing orders in kitchen and display them on some cafeteria hall screens in real time

name: ecommerce-microservices-rabbitmq
description: A microservices-based e-commerce simulation utilizing RabbitMQ for asynchronous communication. The system includes Order, Inventory, and Email services, designed to operate independently while ensuring efficient coordination and scalability.

name: MicroServices_project
description: TravelConnect is a microservices-based hotel management system with secure user, hotel, and rating services. Built with Spring Boot and Okta auth, it offers a scalable solution for booking and review platforms.

name: GoMicro-Distributed-Suite
description: A scalable distributed microservice system with Go and integrated technologies.

name: loan-management-system-grpc
description: A microservices-based Loan Management System API built with gRPC, Golang, Gin, and MongoDB. The system employs JWT for secure authentication, with tokens stored in cookies. Key features include modular microservices for managing user authentication, loan applications, and a digital wallet for handling transactions and balances.

name: smart-healthcare-management-system
description: A comprehensive microservices-based healthcare management system implementing best practices and design patterns, including Saga, CQRS, gRPC, event-driven architecture, and more. Built with Spring Boot, Docker, Kubernetes, and integrated with monitoring and logging tools.

name: Order-Management-System
description: This project is a microservices-based Order Management System (OMS) built with Go. It leverages Docker Compose for orchestration and integrates external services like RabbitMQ for messaging and Jaeger for distributed tracing. The OMS also incorporates Stripe for payment processing.

name: Debra-Event-Management-System
description: A scalable, service-oriented app for managing events, ticketing, sales, and partner integration. Built with a microservices architecture, it offers modular services, a REST API, and seamless deployment with Docker and Kubernetes. Features include event scheduling, ticket management, and comprehensive testing.

name: Mediconnect_WebApp
description: MediConnect is a healthcare management system that facilitates seamless patient-doctor interactions and appointment scheduling. Built with a microservices architecture, it ensures secure access to medical records and efficient management of healthcare services.

name: RealTime-Fraud-Detection
description: The Real-Time Fraud Detection System is designed to detect fraudulent transactions in real-time. Built using a microservice architecture and deployed on AWS, it efficiently handles transaction processing with Kafka, provides real-time notifications with WebSockets, and persists transaction data with PostgreSQL.
